<li id="cite_note-JaneTompkins-42">^ <a href="#cite_ref-JaneTompkins_42-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JaneTompkins_42-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JaneTompkins_42-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-JaneTompkins_42-3" title=""><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="http://web.princeton.edu/sites/english/NEH/TOMPKINS.HTM" class="external text" title="http://web.princeton.edu/sites/english/NEH/TOMPKINS.HTM" rel="nofollow">"Sentimental Power: Uncle Tom's Cabin and the Politics of Literary History"</a> by Jane Tompkins, from <i>In Sensational Designs: The Cultural Work of American Fiction</i>, 1790–1860. New York: Oxford UP, 1985. Pp. 122–146.</li>
